other_tests.findings: Significant variations from baseline were observed in parameters of best-fit Naka-Rushton function; Vmax was notably higher, and K was 0.14 log units lower than baseline at 2 hours after administration.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Vmax increased by 63.1% in the right eye and 36.5% in the left eye compared to baseline; K decreased by 0.14 log unit at 2 hours.
